name: "Kien Giang"
text:
"I came here with a friend after a nice hike at Percy Warner and ordered the rare steak pho along with an Vietnamese Iced Coffee and was mildly surprised to say that it was just as authentic as the best pho places in Los Angeles (which is saying a lot).  The steak came out rare (which for a lot of pho places is never the case despite the printing on the menu) and the coffee was served very uniquely in a drop container that I had to pour into a cup of ice myself. Not that the work was troublesome, but it was the first time I had ever seen the coffee served in that fashion and the pricing was pretty fair.

But like some other people have mentioned, the service here can be a hit or miss. I've come several times before and on some days it's just the regular routine of ordering, eating, paying, and out. On some days however, service can be down right awful when the staff seems to be having a bad day and it almost seems as if they take it out on you. It hasn't happened to me often, but in some of the worst scenarios, they don't even wipe the table very clean before they "order" you to sit down. Despite that though, I'd still come back here to get a bowl of good 'ol fashion pho.

Food: 5
Pricing: 4
Service: 3"

name: "NY Pizza Grill"
text: "What a joke of a place. Placed an online order around 2:30pm on a Saturday afternoon. After an hour or so with no food, I call, no answer (to a cell phone mind you). I decide to take a trip there to see what's going on (since my credit card was charged). They said they just opened, even though the website said they've been open since noon. Ok, looks like a glitch in the system that left me hungry. No problem, you would think they would try and resolve the issue by offering to make the food, or giving me some sort of discount/credit/whatever to make me happy. Instead the guy grabs the order off the printer and says I need to call their online ordering vender to get my money back. Talk about terrible customer service. They are destined for failure."

name: "Farmhaus Restaurant"
text:
"Bacon Wrapped Meatloaf Blue Plate Lunch last week was almost too good to be true. Two giant portions of the best meatloaf ever, a giant dollop of taters and honey glazed carrots that would rival my grammas for only ten bucks!??

Farmhaus is the only place in the area that I can think of that offers superior food in a very welcoming atmosphere. Like I said in my previous review, it feels like coming home to the dinner table. And, eating lunch with three blue collar Americuhans over some fancy food didn't feel out of place at all. Everyone was extremely happy driving away in their T shirts and trucks with full bellies for ten bucks."

name: "Casita Taqueria"
text:
"I love this taco joint!
I'd put the atmosphere right in between the Taco Bus, and Red Mesa. We've been here twice, and will continue to return!
Best carnitas tacos and guacamole in town! (if you've found better, please let me know)
All of their tacos are made with their homemade corn tortillas. Fillings are plentiful and delicious. 
Dog friendly patio dining. 
Beer, wine, sangria!"

name: "Tailgate Brewery - East Nashville"
text: "As a frequenter, I had high hopes as the West Nashville and Midtown location are our favorites. I always get PBMS nitro- it was kind of flat, along with the other IPA we got. One of the things we love about Tailgate is the personable service. The bar service was equal to going to broadway- order, get the drink, and they walk away after you get it. I'm not expecting a full conversation but some interaction would be nice- especially since it's a new location. "Hey, how are y'all? Have you been to Tailgate before? Would you like to sample anything? This is what we have new, you should try it?" BASIC restaurant conversation- we got none. I would have asked for a new beer if it didn't take having to reach over the counter just to flag down the bartender in order to order our pizza (for which we got charged $1.99 for swapping a meat- that we do at other locations with no charge). Pizza was lacking toppings too. I would suggest y'all get on the same page for every location. I don't mind paying extra for ranch when it's homemade (like other locations) but not a fan when it's from a jar. We just hurried up and left to go elsewhere. Don't think y'all were ready to open yet- maybe we will come back in 6 months..."
